reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 3, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Super cute sprinkler, daughter loved it!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewText: We bought this for hot summer days, since we don’t have a pool. Our 2 year old loves it! She loves to play with the flowers, fill up cups with the water and it’s easy to adjust how much water comes out. We got so much use out of it during the summer and can’t wait to take it out once it warms up.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 17, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works great - toddlers love it!
reviews.reviewText: My two year old loves this! Worked great right out of the box. Turned the water up high and the sprinkler handled great. Lots of spray shooting way up there (the kids loved it). Equally fun with the water just “cracked” on for a low spray... which is how we use it the majority of the time (as not to waste water). Good buy, easy to use, lots of fun.Also - I hooked it up to our garden hose which is on a hose reel. Based on other reviews, I was anticipating a “low trickle” and planned to add a “y” in with a short piece of hose... but when I tried it on our “regular” hose (which is on the reel) - it worked perfectly.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars cute fun sprinkler but low sprinkler
reviews.reviewText: I bought this for my 4 and a half yr old granddaughter. She did enjoy it, especially jumping over it and dancing around it. And it cooled her off on a very hot day. The good: I love Melissa & Doug products because I can rely on them being well made and good for children. This is a pretty sprinkler, though some may find it more attractive to the girls.. I think there is a dragon one some boys might like better. The not so good: the fountain of water was much lower than either of us expected. I thought it would go up high and splash her whole body. But it was quite low, just 2 or 3 feet up in the air, even with water on full power. We found something to set it up one (a bucket turned upside down) so the water would be higher. The other thing to watch out for is that it attaches to a hose, so the children have to be careful not to trip on the hose. But thats probably true for all sprinklers. One more thought...in California we are still careful about water usage so it might be best for people with lawns or areas that need water (I dont have a lawn) so you aren't wasting the water.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars a decorative water toy
reviews.reviewText: Bought it for my kids and it worked as expected. The stems were a bit stiff but I think that was needed to make the toy last longer. My kids enjoyed it so that's all I need to say that this was a good item.
Ordered for my 2 year old. It's smaller in size then I imagined, that's not a issue, it's a really nice size. It's made well, and looks better than in the pictures.
My 2 year old is absolutely in love with this product. She is obbsseed with water. I am so happy with this product It's so cute.

I was a bit hesitant because I saw some reviews claiming their hose didn’t fit, but I thought I’d give it a chance since the toy seemed sturdy and I like Melissa and Doug. But sure enough, my absolutely normal and standard hose didn’t fit at all, it was spinning freely on the threads. Lucky me, I had an unused 4-feet hose at my disposal, and it fits perfectly. As a bonus, I can leave the small hose attached on the toy at all time and disconnect it from my longer hose, so I’m less likely to break the plastic fitting of the toy. (Here’s the hose I use : https://www.amazon.ca/-/fr/gp/product/B00167U0PG/ref=ppx_yo_dt_b_search_asin_title?ie=UTF8&psc=1)As for the toy itself, it was shooting 10 feet in the air and all the way onto the patio at first, so I had to crank the pressure down a lot. I really don’t understand why some have complained about getting only tiny jets at best.The toy seems durable, and I like that the flowers and rods are made of silicone. The kids can stumble on them without breaking them or hurting their fragile little toes, which is a plus. My 4 years old really likes it and it is already helping her to conquer her fear of getting sprayed on by a jet of water.
It's a fun sprinkler, the kids love it. The holes in the flowers are a bit big and the water starts to pool fast around it but other than that it's great.
I was expecting something larger than this. It is very tiny.
